    "body": "It seems that one can't declare np.ndarray in cython.locals in .pxd files. It works with memoryviews but not with np.ndarray. However, there are cases where we need np.ndarray.\r\n\r\nIn notsupported.py\r\n```\r\nimport numpy as np\r\n\r\ndef func():\r\n    arr = np.ones(2)\r\n    return arr\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn notsupported.pxd\r\n```\r\nimport cython\r\n\r\nimport numpy as np\r\ncimport numpy as np\r\n\r\n@cython.locals(arr=np.ndarray[np.int_t, ndim=1])\r\ncpdef func()\r\n```\r\n\r\nError log:\r\n```\r\nError compiling Cython file:\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n...\r\nimport cython\r\n\r\nimport numpy as np\r\ncimport numpy as np\r\n\r\n@cython.locals(arr=np.ndarray[np.int_t, ndim=1])\r\n                                           ^\r\n------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nnotsupported.pxd:6:44: Expected ']', found '='\r\n```\r\n\r\nCouldn't it be supported? What is the alternative?",
    "closed_at": null,
